726341f-a.title: Queens: College Point Park - [Chisholm Mansion.]
726341f-a.text:
College Point Park (Queens): The Chisholm Mansion, built in 1848. Mayor La Guardia used this place in 1937 as his Summer City
Mail.
P. L. Sperr  March 12, 1932
726341f-a.folder: College Point Park & [Chisholm Mansion.], Queens, NY

725024f-a.text:
14th Avenue, at the N. W. corner of 121st Street, showing a private home, erected at the turn of the twentieth century. It first appears on a 1909 atlas and stands on land formerly belonging to Herman Funkel (1873-1891).
P. L. Sperr  March 16, 1932
